description:
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide business support to the Service Line Manager, Clinical Director and Matron to assist in the delivery of safe and effective clinical services within the Cardiology service line, ensuring that all Cardiology targets, deadlines and objectives are delivered as appropriate. They will have line management responsibility for direct reports and ensure all Trust policies and procedures (in particular the Trust’s Patient Access Policy) are applied within the service line. The post holder will assume delegated responsibility for the delivery of financial, activity, waiting list and waiting time targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What we need from you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·         Proven experience working as an administrative in an NHS setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·         Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.         Excellent time management and organisational skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During this pandemic we are fastracking our recruitment process but will still require:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·         Proof of Right to Work in the UK  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·         An Enhanced DBS &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;·         Occupational Health Clearance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To apply for this role please complete the application box below and attach your CV.&lt;/p&gt;
